==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alembic
<hw>A*lem"bic</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*l⟦ecr⟧m"b⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>alambic</ets> (cf. Sp. <ets>alambique</ets>), Ar.
<ets>al-anb⟦imac⟧q</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>'a`mbix</grk> cup, cap of a
still. The cap or head was the <ets>alembic</ets> proper. Cf.
<er>Limbec</er>.]</ety> <def>An apparatus formerly used in distillation,
usually made of glass or metal. It has mostly given place to the
<xex>retort</xex> and <xex>worm still</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
<note>Used also metaphorically.⟦br⟧
⟦br⟧
<q>The <qex>alembic</qex> of a great poet's imagination.</q>
<rj><qau>Brimley.</qau></rj></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alembroth</ent>⟦br⟧
